<plot>This brief television production shows the process of turning live minks in cages into dead minks that you can wear in the winter. This includes the slaughtering, the trade of the unprocessed furs, and the design and sales of the final product, with interviews with key players in every part of the process. The film is very neutral, but still rather unsettling due to the pictures of furs being torn off the animals we saw sitting in their cages moments before.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?370969</url></doc>
